predicates.label: allValuesFrom
predicates.description: The property that determines the class that a universal property restriction refers to.

predicates.label: annotatedProperty
predicates.description: The property that determines the predicate of an annotated axiom or annotated annotation.

predicates.label: annotatedSource
predicates.description: The property that determines the subject of an annotated axiom or annotated annotation.

predicates.label: annotatedTarget
predicates.description: The property that determines the object of an annotated axiom or annotated annotation.

predicates.label: assertionProperty
predicates.description: The property that determines the predicate of a negative property assertion.

predicates.label: backwardCompatibleWith
predicates.description: The annotation property that indicates that a given ontology is backward compatible with another ontology.

predicates.label: bottomDataProperty
predicates.description: The data property that does not relate any individual to any data value.

predicates.label: bottomObjectProperty
predicates.description: The object property that does not relate any two individuals.

predicates.label: cardinality
predicates.description: The property that determines the cardinality of an exact cardinality restriction.

predicates.label: complementOf
predicates.description: The property that determines that a given class is the complement of another class.

predicates.label: datatypeComplementOf
predicates.description: The property that determines that a given data range is the complement of another data range with respect to the data domain.

predicates.label: deprecated
predicates.description: The annotation property that indicates that a given entity has been deprecated.

predicates.label: differentFrom
predicates.description: The property that determines that two given individuals are different.

predicates.label: disjointUnionOf
predicates.description: The property that determines that a given class is equivalent to the disjoint union of a collection of other classes.

predicates.label: disjointWith
predicates.description: The property that determines that two given classes are disjoint.

predicates.label: distinctMembers
predicates.description: The property that determines the collection of pairwise different individuals in a owl:AllDifferent axiom.

predicates.label: equivalentClass
predicates.description: The property that determines that two given classes are equivalent, and that is used to specify datatype definitions.

predicates.label: equivalentProperty
predicates.description: The property that determines that two given properties are equivalent.

predicates.label: hasKey
predicates.description: The property that determines the collection of properties that jointly build a key.

predicates.label: hasSelf
predicates.description: The property that determines the property that a self restriction refers to.

predicates.label: hasValue
predicates.description: The property that determines the individual that a has-value restriction refers to.

predicates.label: imports
predicates.description: The property that is used for importing other ontologies into a given ontology.

predicates.label: incompatibleWith
predicates.description: The annotation property that indicates that a given ontology is incompatible with another ontology.

predicates.label: intersectionOf
predicates.description: The property that determines the collection of classes or data ranges that build an intersection.

predicates.label: inverseOf
predicates.description: The property that determines that two given properties are inverse.

predicates.label: maxCardinality
predicates.description: The property that determines the cardinality of a maximum cardinality restriction.

predicates.label: maxQualifiedCardinality
predicates.description: The property that determines the cardinality of a maximum qualified cardinality restriction.

predicates.label: members
predicates.description: The property that determines the collection of members in either a owl:AllDifferent, owl:AllDisjointClasses or owl:AllDisjointProperties axiom.

predicates.label: minCardinality
predicates.description: The property that determines the cardinality of a minimum cardinality restriction.

predicates.label: minQualifiedCardinality
predicates.description: The property that determines the cardinality of a minimum qualified cardinality restriction.

predicates.label: onClass
predicates.description: The property that determines the class that a qualified object cardinality restriction refers to.

predicates.label: onDataRange
predicates.description: The property that determines the data range that a qualified data cardinality restriction refers to.

predicates.label: onDatatype
predicates.description: The property that determines the datatype that a datatype restriction refers to.

predicates.label: oneOf
predicates.description: The property that determines the collection of individuals or data values that build an enumeration.

predicates.label: onProperties
predicates.description: The property that determines the n-tuple of properties that a property restriction on an n-ary data range refers to.

predicates.label: onProperty
predicates.description: The property that determines the property that a property restriction refers to.

predicates.label: priorVersion
predicates.description: The annotation property that indicates the predecessor ontology of a given ontology.

predicates.label: propertyChainAxiom
predicates.description: The property that determines the n-tuple of properties that build a sub property chain of a given property.

predicates.label: propertyDisjointWith
predicates.description: The property that determines that two given properties are disjoint.

predicates.label: qualifiedCardinality
predicates.description: The property that determines the cardinality of an exact qualified cardinality restriction.

predicates.label: sameAs
predicates.description: The property that determines that two given individuals are equal.

predicates.label: someValuesFrom
predicates.description: The property that determines the class that an existential property restriction refers to.

predicates.label: sourceIndividual
predicates.description: The property that determines the subject of a negative property assertion.

predicates.label: targetIndividual
predicates.description: The property that determines the object of a negative object property assertion.

predicates.label: targetValue
predicates.description: The property that determines the value of a negative data property assertion.

predicates.label: topDataProperty
predicates.description: The data property that relates every individual to every data value.

predicates.label: topObjectProperty
predicates.description: The object property that relates every two individuals.

predicates.label: unionOf
predicates.description: The property that determines the collection of classes or data ranges that build a union.

predicates.label: versionInfo
predicates.description: The annotation property that provides version information for an ontology or another OWL construct.

predicates.label: versionIRI
predicates.description: The property that identifies the version IRI of an ontology.

predicates.label: withRestrictions
predicates.description: The property that determines the collection of facet-value pairs that define a datatype restriction.
